{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀπέραντος</b>, ον, <br /> (περαίνω) <b>boundless, infinite,</b> of space, πεδίον[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 8.38 (who also has ἀπείραντος ἀλκά “P.” 9.35); πόντου κλῇδ᾽ ἀ. 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Medea” 213 (Lyric poetry); τὸν ἀέρα τόνδ᾽ ὄντ᾽ ἀ. 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 393; ὁδός 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 147c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of time, <b>endless,</b> τὸ χρῆμα τῶν νυκτῶν ὅσον· ἀπέραντον[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 3; χρόνος 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Politicus” 302a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of number, <b>countless, infinite,</b> ἀ. ἀριθμὸς ἀνθρώπων[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Criti.” 119a; ἀ. κακά [prev. author] “R.” 591d, +others; λῦπαι 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Solon” 7; πένθη “Fab.” 17\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; <b>unlimited,</b> τιμωρίαι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 23.39\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; generally, of events, business, etc., ἀπέραντον ἦν there was <b>no end to it,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.36; μακρὸν καὶ ἀ. φαίνεται 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Nicomachea” 1101a26\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀπέραντα περαίνειν represent as concluded <b>what is not concluded,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Philops.” 9\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] (with allusion to <i>signification</i> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 111); μηδὲν ἀβασάνιστον μηδ᾽ ἀ. 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 4.75.3. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<i>adverb</i>, τὸ ἀπεράντως διεστηκός of <b>unlimited</b> dimensions, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Physica” 204b21, “Metaphorical” 1066b33. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>allowing no escape, whence none can pass,</b> Τάρτα